---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import MapView from "../components/MapView.astro";
import {
  SERIES_START,
  SERIES_END,
  LATEST_NCR_PCT,
  NCR_LGU_COUNT,
  CANOPY_MODEL_F1,
  GOLD_LABEL_N,
} from "../lib/series";
---
<Base
  title="Leaves.PH · explore Metro Manila's tree canopy"
  description="Explore Metro Manila's tree canopy on an interactive map. Drag the year, find your barangay, click any tree. Open, reproducible Sentinel-2 measurements across the 17 NCR cities, 2019 to 2026."
  pathname="/"
  fullBleed={true}
>
  <MapView />

  <!-- The finding + how-we-measured. Keeps the credibility, the indexable text,
       and the route into the full report one click below the map. -->
  <section class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-5 sm:px-10 py-12 border-t border-ink-900">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1.5fr)_minmax(0,1fr)] gap-x-14 gap-y-8">
      <div class="max-w-[60ch]">
        <p class="kicker text-sepia-500 mb-3">the finding</p>
        <h2 class="font-display text-ink-900 leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.012em]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);">
          About a tenth of Metro Manila is under tree canopy, and most of it sits in one city.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-[15px] text-ink-700 leading-[1.62] mt-4">
          Across the {NCR_LGU_COUNT} cities of the National Capital Region the area-weighted tree cover is roughly nine to ten per cent (the latest year reads {LATEST_NCR_PCT.toFixed(2)} per cent and is provisional). Quezon City alone, anchored by the La Mesa watershed, carries the regional average; pull it out and the figure roughly halves. These are annual snapshots from satellite imagery, not a measured loss series.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[15px] text-ink-700 leading-[1.62] mt-4">
          Every 30-metre pixel is classified by a model trained on {GOLD_LABEL_N} hand-checked high-resolution points (F1 {CANOPY_MODEL_F1.toFixed(2)}), and the whole pipeline is open and reproducible from a clean clone. The map is a tree-cover estimate with a known grass-and-scrub margin, not a pixel-exact census.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-7 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-6 gap-y-3">
          <a href="/report" class="inline-block bg-forest-700 text-paper px-4 py-2 font-mono text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.12em] no-underline hover:bg-forest-900 transition-colors">Read the full report</a>
          <a href="/methodology" class="font-mono text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-umber-700 no-underline border-b border-umber-500 hover:border-umber-700">How we measured &rarr;</a>
          <a href="/data" class="font-mono text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-umber-700 no-underline border-b border-umber-500 hover:border-umber-700">Download the data &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="text-sepia-500 lg:border-l lg:border-ink-300 lg:pl-10">
        <div class="marginal !border-t-0 !mt-0 !pt-0">
          <p class="text-ink-700 font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-[10px] mb-1">Scope</p>
          <p>The {NCR_LGU_COUNT} cities of the National Capital Region (16 cities plus Pateros), per PSA boundaries, with 892 barangays for the finer view. {SERIES_START} to {SERIES_END}.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="marginal mt-6">
          <p class="text-ink-700 font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-[10px] mb-1">Sources</p>
          <p>Sentinel-2 via Google Earth Engine. Meta canopy height v2 via AWS Open Data. Boundaries via OpenStreetMap and PSA. All public, all open.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="marginal mt-6">
          <p class="text-ink-700 font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-[10px] mb-1">Corrections</p>
          <p>Spot something off for your area? <a href="https://github.com/xmpuspus/leaves-ph/issues" class="text-umber-700 underline decoration-umber-500/50 underline-offset-2">File a correction</a> with a source and we will review it.</p>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
